{
  "text": "We developed assays to assess humoral immunity to three tumor antigens expressed in ovarian cancer: p53, HER-2/neu, and topoisomerase II\u2423. All three of these proteins have been shown to be immunogenic in individuals with ovarian cancer. [20] [CITATION_1] [22] In addition, expression of these proteins in ovarian cancers is associated with a poorer prognosis. Between 30% and 50% of advanced-stage ovarian cancers express p53, and expression of the protein is associated with decreased survival.",
  "citation_candidates": [
